<!-- ══════════════════════════════════════
     INTRO — What Makes Thermador Different
══════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">01 — About Thermador</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">German Engineering in an LA Kitchen</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">
      Thermador has been building professional-grade home appliances since 1916 — the original wall oven was theirs. Today, as part of BSH Home Appliances (the same group behind Bosch and Gaggenau), they manufacture some of the most technically sophisticated kitchen equipment available to homeowners. The Star® burner that reduces cooking time by up to 50%. The ExtraLow® simmer setting that holds a precise 100°F without scorching. Steam-convection wall ovens that professional chefs actually want in their homes. Flush-mount column refrigerators designed to disappear into custom millwork.
    </p>
    <p class="section-lead">
      All of that engineering creates extraordinary performance. It also creates appliances that require a technician who understands the technology — not just someone who's seen the name before. Our techs have serviced Thermador ranges in Bel Air estates, cooling columns in Brentwood kitchen remodels, and steam ovens in Malibu beach houses. We carry OEM Thermador parts on every truck and provide a flat-rate written quote before any work begins.
    </p>

    <div class="tip-block tip-climate">
      <div class="tip-label">🌊 LA Climate Note</div>
      <div class="tip-text">Southern California's combination of coastal humidity (Malibu, Pacific Palisades, Santa Monica) and Santa Ana wind-driven dust (San Fernando Valley, Pasadena) creates specific stress patterns on Thermador condenser coils, door gaskets, and burner igniters. We account for this on every service call — it's part of the diagnosis, not an afterthought.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ══════════════════════════════════════
     SERVICES — Appliances We Repair
══════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">02 — Services</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Every Thermador Appliance We Service</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">Same-day service available across Los Angeles County. We stock parts for all current and legacy Thermador models.</p>

    <div class="services-grid">
      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🔥</div>
        <div class="service-name">Range &amp; Cooktop Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Gas ranges, Pro Harmony® dual-fuel ranges, induction cooktops, and all Star® burner configurations. We carry igniter modules, burner caps, valve manifold parts, and control boards for models back to 2008.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: igniter not sparking · burner won't light · gas not flowing · surface element failure · LP to natural gas conversion</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🌡️</div>
        <div class="service-name">Wall Oven Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Single, double, and combination wall ovens. Steam ovens and steam-convection ovens. We diagnose and repair heating elements, door gaskets, convection fans, temperature sensors, and electronic control panels.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: oven not heating · temperature fluctuation · convection fan failure · door not sealing · steam function not working · error codes</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">❄️</div>
        <div class="service-name">Built-In Refrigerator Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Flush-mount column refrigerators, bottom-freezer units, side-by-side, and under-counter models. Thermador's Freedom® column refrigerators require specialized handling to avoid damaging custom millwork during service.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: not cooling · ice maker failure · temperature swings · frost buildup · compressor issues · thermistor failure · door gasket worn</div>
      </div>

